- 1.0.3 | Mar 02 2026:

  -- New Features --

[New] install-bats.sh: SHA256 checksum verification for all three pinned
      tarballs (bats-core, bats-support, bats-assert) — download integrity
      backstop compensating for disabled TLS verification on legacy OS
[New] README: migration guide with version-specific upgrade notes for
      consumers — covers BATS 1.13.0 run-variable unset breaking change,
      SHA256 checksum verification, parallelism reduction, CLI strictness
[New] 60 new self-tests — CLI argument parsing (20), build/clean/routing
      (19), execution modes (12), install-bats.sh (7), _batsman_done
      flag (2); 133 tests total

  -- Bug Fixes --

[Fix] Harden CLI argument parsing — shift guards on value-consuming flags,
      batsman_run() propagates parse/build failures, --timeout numeric
      validation, unknown --flags warn instead of silently routing to
      direct mode, end-of-options (--) support
[Fix] install-bats.sh: harden download pipeline — file-based download
      replacing stdout pipe (prevents corruption on fallback retry),
      set -o pipefail, network timeouts (wget --timeout=60, curl
      --connect-timeout 30 --max-time 120)
[Fix] --help and --version now return instead of exit in sourced library —
      prevents process termination when called from sourced context; adds
      _batsman_done flag checked by batsman_run() for clean short-circuit
[Fix] Add nproc fallback chain (nproc || sysctl -n hw.logicalcpu || echo 1)
      in run-tests-core.sh and Makefile.tests — enables macOS host support
      where GNU nproc is unavailable
[Fix] self-test.yml: widen push branch pattern from '1.*' to '[0-9]*.*' —
      CI triggers on any version branch, not just 1.x
[Fix] Makefile.tests parallel xargs targets: wrap commands with sh -c to
      emit per-OS failure banners to stderr — xargs -P exit 123 no longer
      hides which OS targets failed
[Fix] Makefile.tests clean-all regex: add hyphen to character class so
      hyphenated project names (e.g., my-project) are matched for image
      cleanup
[Fix] Documentation accuracy pass — correct help text, README, and
      CHANGELOG for parallelism, TLS fallback, container naming, and
      formatter behavior

  -- Changes --

[Change] Demote default parallelism from nproc*2 to nproc for both
      intra-OS and cross-OS parallelism — prevents compounding container
      storms on test-all-parallel targets
